After you hit an enemy with your weapon, hold down ZL+ZR (ClassicController) or C+Z (WiiMote+Nunchuck) buttons then press the following directional buttons: UP to teleport the monster to your area, LEFT to increase HP to 10,000 (1HP/Capture if with B button), LEFT+DOWN to make it sleep (pitfall trapped if with B button), DOWN to disrupt it (stun them too if with B button), DOWN+RIGHT to shock it (shock trapped if with B button) and RIGHT to receive 100point damage (kill it if with B button). Hold down ZL+ZR+Y or C+Z+1 buttons to make the monster slow down.

Modify Wyvern Team Takedown quest in Arena [Doudley]
4A000000 901E02A0
3800002C 0000232F
1200013A 00000032
1200035A 000000E6
12000398 00000001
10000314 00000001
10000318 00000024
1000031A 00000064
120003F8 00000002
1000031C 00000002
10000320 00000025
10000322 00000064
E0000000 80008000
Change the value in the following order: hex digit "32" is 50mins, "00E6" is 230 death penalty, the two "01" is (Rathian) the first large monster, "24" is (36) his level and "64" is (100%) his size percentage, the two "02" is (Rathalos) the second large monster, "25" is (37) his level and "64" is (100%) his size percentage. Here are the monster's digits: 01=Rathian, 02=Rathalos, 03=Qurupeco, 04=Gigginox, 05=Barioth, 06=Diablos, 07=Deviljho, 08=Barroth, 09=Uragaan, 0C=Great Jaggi, 0E=Great Baggi, 10=Royal Ludroth (on 2nd monster slot only) and 13=Agnaktor.

Here are the monster's digits: 01=Rathian, 02=Rathalos, 03=Qurupeco, 04=Gigginox, 05=Barioth, 06=Diablos, 07=Deviljho, 08=Barroth, 09=Uragaan, 0C=Great Jaggi, 0E=Great Baggi, 10=Royal Ludroth (on 2nd monster slot only) and 13=Agnaktor.

Monster Speed Modifier [Stuff]
C212F4D8 00000002
3C00XXXX 901F07C0
C01F07C0 00000000
XXXX = first half of the floating point(in hex)...no real need for the second half. Let me know if you need the second half
use http://geckocodes.org/index.php?arsenal=3 for hex&lt;&gt;float
3F80(0000) = normal, 3FC0 = faster, 4040 = OMG FFFFF!!! I don't wanna know what happens with bigger numbers.
3F00 = pretty darn slow, 2C00 = everything was frozen. The game froze at some point.
Play around with it. You might not want to go lower than 3E00..

Wiimote Button Activator [Bully@Wiiplaza]
2865941A YYYYZZZZ
*Credits to Doudley*
*YYYY = FFFF - ZZZZ*
*ZZZZ Values*
0004 = Z
0008 = C
0010 = 2
0020 = 1
0040 = -
0080 = +
0100 = B
0200 = A
0400 = D-PAD_RIGHT
0800 = D-PAD_LEFT
1000 = D-PAD_DOWN
2000 = D-PAD_UP
8000 = HOME

Hunter x Gatherer - make your own 2 Active Skills set [Doudley]
48000000 806BBC74
DE000000 90149015
160005F2 00000018
00EE00EE 00EE00EE
00EE00EE 00EE00EE
01010101 01010101
38000018 00FF0100
160005F2 00000010
00EE00EE 00EE00EE
00EE00EE 00EE00EE
E0000000 80008000
You can have a full set of Active Skills (8 in total) for Sheathed Weapon (Top 8 "EE"s) and another set for Drawn Weapon (Bottom 8 "EE"s). Replace the "EE"s with the desired skill you want, look for "Active Skill Digits" at Mod Digits section.

00891B36 000000??

Belts 007D Skill Power 5 [Skiller]
00891B37 0000007F

@@PAGE: Mod Digits

Controller Pad Digits

For Player 1
Replace ?
6593E8 = WiiMote
6593DC = Classic

For Player 2
Replace ?
659738 = WiiMote
65972C = Classic

XXXX is for button(s)
Replace X
http://www.codemasters-project.net/members/Skiller/CMP/Jokerwii.htm

MMMM is for mask
Replace M
Hex digits FFFF minus your button(s) XXXX the result is MMMM.
A mask in button activators makes a code to allow use of other buttons w/o deactivating it.

*1. This code will only activate when you do weapon damage to a monster. (excludes some Bowgun shots, kicking, gesture hits, Bombs, Throwing knives, Mounted Bowguns, etc...)
*2. Sometimes the code activates if any monster receives a damage, not only by you. (including Cha-Cha)
*3. If you moved to another "Area", the target will change according to the monster list.
*4. This code can be used with Changeable Target View and Fixed Target View(with C-pad support) codes.

MID's Fixed Target View (No C-pad support) [Skiller]
017C4FFC 000000XX

MID's Fixed Target View (with C-pad support) [Skiller]
28ZZZZZZ 0000YYYY
017C4FFC 000000XX
E0000000 80009000
28ZZZZZZ 0000YYYY
017C4FFC 000000XX
E0000000 80009000
For XX put 01 to 0C. (01 is the First Boss/monster, 02 is the 2nd)
For ZZZZZZ get it here, for YYYY choose your buttons here.
*If the code is applied to a higher number and was activated in-game while the monster is not yet shown in the monster list, the target view will return back to 00.
*Use 00 value to make a Resetter code.

NOTE: You can change the color values for Text Color Switcher code, just change the digits in the address (e.g. 017C4FFA 000000XX) and replace XX with the list below.
Text Color Values:
00 = White
01 = Black
02 = Red
03 = Green
04 = Cyan
05 = Yellow
06 = Orange
07 = Pink
08 = Sienna
09 = LightGrey/Silver
0A = Grey
0B = Deep Orange/Gold
0C = RosyBrown
0D = DarkRed
0E = RoyalBlue
0F = BubblegumPink
